bug.short_desc: The web browser preview shows garbled values for Emojis in case of libreoffice calc and impress.
bug.cf_doc_type: If docs needed, set a value

long_desc.thetext:
Description of problem: The web browser preview shows garbled values for Emojis in case of libreoffice calc and impress. Tried some emojis with libreoffice calc and impress. When the web preview was selected, the emojis were seen garbled. Export to pdf worked fine without any issue. Also the web preview was proper with libreoffice writer. Please refer attached screenshot.
Version-Release number of selected component (if applicable): libreoffice-core-5.2.2.2-1.fc25.x86_64 Fedora 25
How reproducible: always
Steps to Reproduce: 1. open libreoffice calc or impress 2. write some emojis using ctrl+shift+e (e.g. ctrl+shift+e+smile) 3. check the web browser preview from menu option.
Actual results: The web browser preview is garbled for emojis.
Expected results: The preview should be proper.
Additional info:
Created attachment 1207967 web browser garbled preview for emojis
presumably the editeng html code isn't utf-16 correct or something
